Last night I was trying to setup a @mail server but the installer kept choking when attempting to connect to my local database.
I am posting here my quick workaround in case you too, dear reader, get a dreaded &ldquo;PDO&rdquo; error message complaining about your attempt to &ldquo; connect to unix:// &ldquo;
Here is I how I solved the issue for @mail: I opened library/Zend/Db/Adapter/Pdo/Abstract.php , found the line that creates the PDO object (&rdquo; new PDO(&hellip; &ldquo;) and, in this example, the first argument passed to the constructor was $dsn.

About 10 months ago, I released this tool, allowing developers to handle ExtJS like &ldquo;managed&rdquo; code in PHP: ExtPHP.
Shortly thereafter, Jack Slocum changed ExtJS&rsquo; licensing model and it all became very muddy but my main question was: &ldquo;As a commercial user, what would the status of the extensions be?&rdquo;
It seems that it&rsquo;s OK to create an extension and not GPL it as long as it doesn&rsquo;t contain any ExtJS original code.
